les to maintain consistency and clarity. I'm focusing on the overall design aesthetic for the component.\n\n\n**Designing Attestation Simulation**\n\nI'm now integrating an attestation process simulation directly into the UI. I've built a button with a spinner to reflect state changes. I'm focusing on the interaction and the visual representation of this simulated process. I'm prioritizing immediate feedback on the attestation attempt.\n\n\n**Refining Hardware Display**\n\nI'm now refining the hardware visualization, specifically incorporating the CPU and RAM metrics within the `WorkspaceCard` component. I've integrated visual indicators, including percentage values and progress bars, for CPU allocation and RAM utilization to provide immediate feedback on resource consumption. This aims to improve the component's functionality and clarity, ensuring a more informative user experience.\n\n\n**Integrating Pulse Metrics**\n\nI'm now integrating pulse metrics such as latency and uptime into the `WorkspaceCard` component. I'm focusing on their visual representation using text, icons, and color-coded indicators for key metrics. I'm prioritizing clarity and readability, ensuring instant understanding of agent health and performance. My goal is to clearly highlight critical performance indicators.\n\n\n**Visualizing Performance Metrics**\n\nI'm now focusing on integrating `pulse` metrics into the `WorkspaceCard`, alongside CPU and RAM. I'm prioritizing the display of latency and uptime using a combination of text, icons, and color-coded indicators for key metrics. The goal is to make critical performance indicators immediately understandable.\n\n\n**Refining Isolation Display**\n\nI'm now integrating contextCache and enclave isolation details directly within the agent's display. I'm focusing on clearly showcasing values and using visual cues to differentiate between \"AMD SEV-SNP\" or \"Intel SGX\" enclaves. I'm prioritizing readability and ease of understanding for the user