ontexts.\n\n\n**Integrating Host Architecture**\n\nI'm now integrating the host architecture details within the Hardware Sandbox Enclave representation. I'm focusing on incorporating the \"Bare-Metal Sovereign Node\" label, the `agent.isolation` data and accompanying descriptions within the `WorkspaceCard`, ensuring clear visual separation and emphasis on enclave boundaries and security contexts. I'm also now focusing on incorporating the new design elements.\n\n\n\n**Visualizing Active Key**\n\nI'm now integrating active key information. I'm focusing on incorporating the \"KEY INDEX LOCK ACTIVE\" badge within the Hardware Sandbox Enclave representation, along with the \"GUEST RUNTIME\" detail and a dynamic agent name label. I am prioritizing a clear and visually distinct representation for immediate comprehension.\n\n\\n\\n\nI'm now integrating key details such as \"KEY INDEX LOCK ACTIVE\" into the Hardware Sandbox Enclave visualization. I'm aiming to provide concise, easily understood key status at a glance, directly within the enclave representation. I'm prioritizing clear visual cues to highlight the current active state of the key.\n\n\n**Presenting Decoupled Diagnostics**\n\nI'm working to integrate a diagnostic section within the WorkspaceCard to address a decoupled state. I'm focusing on clearly presenting the need for potential intervention, such as physical access or register resets, as well as providing instructions for ticket submission, with HSM key reset and RAM scaling instructions.\n\n\n"}}
